Nourishing your legendary mountain adventures. Margies Haas breakfast is a tribute to the World War II local home cook, Margie Haas, who welcomed soldiers from the 10th Mountain Division into her home.
Welcome to where aprs begins. Capturing the revelry and passion for our mountains, Revel Lounge celebrates your days adventures with hand-crafted cocktails and Colorado-inspired cuisine.

Cucina offers mountain-comfort cuisine with a laid back and family-friendly atmosphere. Known for its heart breakfast buffet before a day up the mountain, Cucina is also the perfect setting for unwinding after a day filled with Vail adventures. Cucinas outdoor fire pit and recently renovated bar draw locals and visitors alike for its stellar family-friendly aprs-ski scene during the winter season. Cucina offers an unbeatable location in the heart of Vail Village.

Just steps from the Eagle Bahn Gondola, in the Arrabelle within Lionshead Village, the Tavern has a creative and delicious array of lunch and dinner selections. Try our quick service walk up bar with dining on the square and gastropub cuisine, or enjoy a reservations only a la carte dining experience on the mountain side and patio. An outdoor patio with breathtaking mountain views, the Tavern is the perfect spot after a day on the mountain!
